[normal]&#xa0;[bold]The roadmap was important in setting out the need for CCS and stating its role as a key technology in the fight against the dangers of climate change. 
[normal]However, the
[normal] roadmap did not set out a route 
[normal]to market for the transportation and storage segments of CCS. Without the delivery of this infrastructure 
[normal]we believe 
[normal]the 
[normal]viability of CCS as an option for decarbonisation is at risk
[normal]. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Key risks to CCS development not addressed by the roadmap include: 
[normal] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]f
[normal]inance and cost (lack of suitable incentives and drivers to encourage projects and make them viable); 
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]storage (the need to provide up-front proven bankable stores, how they can be accessed and delivered to the market
[normal]);
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]development of transport and storage
[normal] infrastructure independent of power generation decisions
[normal];
[normal] and
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]the lack of real power sector economics and drivers (and therefore desire) for CCS deployment.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]As discussed earlier, we suggest that any policy developed for CCS needs to enable opportunistic 
[normal]deployment for all sectors that can make use of the infrastructure.  This means creating incentives and pathways that can work as proxies for the business models existing in other countries.  We believe the whole financial model for delivery also needs to 
[normal]be re-explored by collaborative regional groups such as the UK, with Norway and the Netherlands.  The North Sea Basin is an asset that can be used for Europe and will be needed to meet European decarbonisation aspirations.  Hence the energy system will nee
[normal]d infrastructure so that CO
[normal]2
[normal] could be transported from countries without the benefit of offshore storage solutions.
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Quite simply we would flag that the IEA has said CCS is essential. 
[normal]To stimulate an industry, by demonstrating the UK’s ability to achieve delivery of CCS
[normal] 
[normal]in a complicated offshore environment, then it will contribute to the confidence that CCS is a “real” 
[normal]solution, both in a European and global context.
